44#if defined(BLOCK_SIZE) && (BLOCK_SIZE & 7)
45#error An illegal block size has been specified.
46#endif
47
48/* Subroutine to set the block size (if variable). The value can be
49 in bytes, with legal values of 16, 24 and 32, or in bits, with
50 legal values of 128, 192 and 256.
51*/
52
53#if !defined(BLOCK_SIZE)
54
55aes_rval aes_set_block_size(unsigned int blen, aes_ctx cx[1])
56{
57#if !defined(FIXED_TABLES)
58#ifdef GLOBALS
59 if(!t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs();
60#else
61 if(!cx->t_ptr || !t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs(cx);
62#endif
63#endif
64 if(((blen & 7) || blen < 16 || blen > 32) && ((blen & 63) || blen < 128 || blen > 256))
65 {
66 cx->n_blk = 0; return aes_bad;
67 }
68 else
69 {
70 cx->n_blk = blen >> (blen < 128 ? 0 : 3); return aes_good;
71 }
72}
73
74#endif
75
76/* Initialise the key schedule from the user supplied key. The key
77 length can be specified in bytes, with legal values of 16, 24
78 and 32, or in bits, with legal values of 128, 192 and 256. These
79 values correspond with Nk values of 4, 6 and 8 respectively.
80
81 The following macros implement a single cycle in the key
82 schedule generation process. The number of cycles needed
83 for each cx->n_col and nk value is:
84
85 nk = 4 5 6 7 8
86 ------------------------------
87 cx->n_col = 4 10 9 8 7 7
88 cx->n_col = 5 14 11 10 9 9
89 cx->n_col = 6 19 15 12 11 11
90 cx->n_col = 7 21 19 16 13 14
91 cx->n_col = 8 29 23 19 17 14
92*/
93
94#define ke4(k,i) \
95{ k[4*(i)+4] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[3],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[4*(i)+5] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
96 k[4*(i)+6] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[4*(i)+7] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
97}
98#define kel4(k,i) \
99{ k[4*(i)+4] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[3],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[4*(i)+5] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
100 k[4*(i)+6] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[4*(i)+7] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
101}
102
103#define ke6(k,i) \
104{ k[6*(i)+ 6] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[5],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[6*(i)+ 7] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
105 k[6*(i)+ 8] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[6*(i)+ 9] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
106 k[6*(i)+10] = ss[4] ^= ss[3]; k[6*(i)+11] = ss[5] ^= ss[4]; \
107}
108#define kel6(k,i) \
109{ k[6*(i)+ 6] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[5],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[6*(i)+ 7] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
110 k[6*(i)+ 8] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[6*(i)+ 9] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
111}
112
113#define ke8(k,i) \
114{ k[8*(i)+ 8] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[7],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[8*(i)+ 9] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
115 k[8*(i)+10] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[8*(i)+11] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
116 k[8*(i)+12] = ss[4] ^= ls_box(ss[3],0); k[8*(i)+13] = ss[5] ^= ss[4]; \
117 k[8*(i)+14] = ss[6] ^= ss[5]; k[8*(i)+15] = ss[7] ^= ss[6]; \
118}
119#define kel8(k,i) \
120{ k[8*(i)+ 8] = ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[7],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[8*(i)+ 9] = ss[1] ^= ss[0]; \
121 k[8*(i)+10] = ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[8*(i)+11] = ss[3] ^= ss[2]; \
122}
123
124#if defined(ENCRYPTION_KEY_SCHEDULE)
125
126aes_rval aes_set_encrypt_key(const unsigned char in_key[], unsigned int klen, aes_ctx cx[1])
127{ aes_32t ss[8];
128
129#if !defined(FIXED_TABLES)
130#ifdef GLOBALS
131 if(!t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs();
132#else
133 if(!cx->t_ptr || !t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs(cx);
134#endif
135#endif
136
137#if !defined(BLOCK_SIZE)
138 if(!cx->n_blk) cx->n_blk = 16;
139#else
140 cx->n_blk = BLOCK_SIZE;
141#endif
142
143 if(((klen & 7) || klen < 16 || klen > 32) && ((klen & 63) || klen < 128 || klen > 256))
144 {
145 cx->n_rnd = 0; return aes_bad;
146 }
147
148 klen >>= (klen < 128 ? 2 : 5);
149 cx->n_blk = (cx->n_blk & ~3) | 1;
150
151 cx->k_sch[0] = ss[0] = word_in(in_key );
152 cx->k_sch[1] = ss[1] = word_in(in_key + 4);
153 cx->k_sch[2] = ss[2] = word_in(in_key + 8);
154 cx->k_sch[3] = ss[3] = word_in(in_key + 12);
155
156#if (BLOCK_SIZE == 16) && (ENC_UNROLL != NONE)
157
158 switch(klen)
159 {
160 case 4:
161 ke4(cx->k_sch, 0); ke4(cx->k_sch, 1);
162 ke4(cx->k_sch, 2); ke4(cx->k_sch, 3);
163 ke4(cx->k_sch, 4); ke4(cx->k_sch, 5);
164 ke4(cx->k_sch, 6); ke4(cx->k_sch, 7);
165 ke4(cx->k_sch, 8); kel4(cx->k_sch, 9);
166 cx->n_rnd = 10; break;
167 case 6:
168 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
169 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
170 ke6(cx->k_sch, 0); ke6(cx->k_sch, 1);
171 ke6(cx->k_sch, 2); ke6(cx->k_sch, 3);
172 ke6(cx->k_sch, 4); ke6(cx->k_sch, 5);
173 ke6(cx->k_sch, 6); kel6(cx->k_sch, 7);
174 cx->n_rnd = 12; break;
175 case 8:
176 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
177 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
178 cx->k_sch[6] = ss[6] = word_in(in_key + 24);
179 cx->k_sch[7] = ss[7] = word_in(in_key + 28);
180 ke8(cx->k_sch, 0); ke8(cx->k_sch, 1);
181 ke8(cx->k_sch, 2); ke8(cx->k_sch, 3);
182 ke8(cx->k_sch, 4); ke8(cx->k_sch, 5);
183 kel8(cx->k_sch, 6);
184 cx->n_rnd = 14; break;
185 default:
186 ;
187 }
188#else
189 cx->n_rnd = (klen > nc ? klen : nc) + 6;
190 { aes_32t i, l;
191 l = (nc * cx->n_rnd + nc - 1) / klen;
192
193 switch(klen)
194 {
195 case 4:
196 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
197 ke4(cx->k_sch, i);
198 break;
199 case 6:
200 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
201 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
202 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
203 ke6(cx->k_sch, i);
204 break;
205 case 8:
206 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
207 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
208 cx->k_sch[6] = ss[6] = word_in(in_key + 24);
209 cx->k_sch[7] = ss[7] = word_in(in_key + 28);
210 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
211 ke8(cx->k_sch, i);
212 break;
213 default:
214 ;
215 }
216 }
217#endif
218
219 return aes_good;
220}
221
222#endif

224#if defined(DECRYPTION_KEY_SCHEDULE)
225
226#if (DEC_ROUND != NO_TABLES)
227#define d_vars dec_imvars
228#define ff(x) inv_mcol(x)
229#else
230#define ff(x) (x)
231#define d_vars
232#endif
233
234#if 1
235#define kdf4(k,i) \
236{ ss[0] = ss[0] ^ ss[2] ^ ss[1] ^ ss[3]; ss[1] = ss[1] ^ ss[3]; ss[2] = ss[2] ^ ss[3]; ss[3] = ss[3]; \
237 ss[4] = ls_box(ss[(i+3) % 4], 3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; ss[i % 4] ^= ss[4]; \
238 ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)]; k[4*(i)+4] = ff(ss[4]); ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+1]; k[4*(i)+5] = ff(ss[4]); \
239 ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+2]; k[4*(i)+6] = ff(ss[4]); ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+3]; k[4*(i)+7] = ff(ss[4]); \
240}
241#define kd4(k,i) \
242{ ss[4] = ls_box(ss[(i+3) % 4], 3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; ss[i % 4] ^= ss[4]; ss[4] = ff(ss[4]); \
243 k[4*(i)+4] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)]; k[4*(i)+5] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+1]; \
244 k[4*(i)+6] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+2]; k[4*(i)+7] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+3]; \
245}
246#define kdl4(k,i) \
247{ ss[4] = ls_box(ss[(i+3) % 4], 3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; ss[i % 4] ^= ss[4]; \
248 k[4*(i)+4] = (ss[0] ^= ss[1]) ^ ss[2] ^ ss[3]; k[4*(i)+5] = ss[1] ^ ss[3]; \
249 k[4*(i)+6] = ss[0]; k[4*(i)+7] = ss[1]; \
250}
251#else
252#define kdf4(k,i) \
253{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[3],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[4*(i)+ 4] = ff(ss[0]); ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[4*(i)+ 5] = ff(ss[1]); \
254 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[4*(i)+ 6] = ff(ss[2]); ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[4*(i)+ 7] = ff(ss[3]); \
255}
256#define kd4(k,i) \
257{ ss[4] = ls_box(ss[3],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; \
258 ss[0] ^= ss[4]; ss[4] = ff(ss[4]); k[4*(i)+ 4] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)]; \
259 ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[4*(i)+ 5] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+ 1]; \
260 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[4*(i)+ 6] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+ 2]; \
261 ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[4*(i)+ 7] = ss[4] ^= k[4*(i)+ 3]; \
262}
263#define kdl4(k,i) \
264{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[3],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[4*(i)+ 4] = ss[0]; ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[4*(i)+ 5] = ss[1]; \
265 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[4*(i)+ 6] = ss[2]; ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[4*(i)+ 7] = ss[3]; \
266}
267#endif
268
269#define kdf6(k,i) \
270{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[5],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[6*(i)+ 6] = ff(ss[0]); ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[6*(i)+ 7] = ff(ss[1]); \
271 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[6*(i)+ 8] = ff(ss[2]); ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[6*(i)+ 9] = ff(ss[3]); \
272 ss[4] ^= ss[3]; k[6*(i)+10] = ff(ss[4]); ss[5] ^= ss[4]; k[6*(i)+11] = ff(ss[5]); \
273}
274#define kd6(k,i) \
275{ ss[6] = ls_box(ss[5],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; \
276 ss[0] ^= ss[6]; ss[6] = ff(ss[6]); k[6*(i)+ 6] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)]; \
277 ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[6*(i)+ 7] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)+ 1]; \
278 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[6*(i)+ 8] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)+ 2]; \
279 ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[6*(i)+ 9] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)+ 3]; \
280 ss[4] ^= ss[3]; k[6*(i)+10] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)+ 4]; \
281 ss[5] ^= ss[4]; k[6*(i)+11] = ss[6] ^= k[6*(i)+ 5]; \
282}
283#define kdl6(k,i) \
284{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[5],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[6*(i)+ 6] = ss[0]; ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[6*(i)+ 7] = ss[1]; \
285 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[6*(i)+ 8] = ss[2]; ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[6*(i)+ 9] = ss[3]; \
286}
287
288#define kdf8(k,i) \
289{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[7],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[8*(i)+ 8] = ff(ss[0]); ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[8*(i)+ 9] = ff(ss[1]); \
290 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[8*(i)+10] = ff(ss[2]); ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[8*(i)+11] = ff(ss[3]); \
291 ss[4] ^= ls_box(ss[3],0); k[8*(i)+12] = ff(ss[4]); ss[5] ^= ss[4]; k[8*(i)+13] = ff(ss[5]); \
292 ss[6] ^= ss[5]; k[8*(i)+14] = ff(ss[6]); ss[7] ^= ss[6]; k[8*(i)+15] = ff(ss[7]); \
293}
294#define kd8(k,i) \
295{ aes_32t g = ls_box(ss[7],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; \
296 ss[0] ^= g; g = ff(g); k[8*(i)+ 8] = g ^= k[8*(i)]; \
297 ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[8*(i)+ 9] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 1]; \
298 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[8*(i)+10] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 2]; \
299 ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[8*(i)+11] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 3]; \
300 g = ls_box(ss[3],0); \
301 ss[4] ^= g; g = ff(g); k[8*(i)+12] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 4]; \
302 ss[5] ^= ss[4]; k[8*(i)+13] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 5]; \
303 ss[6] ^= ss[5]; k[8*(i)+14] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 6]; \
304 ss[7] ^= ss[6]; k[8*(i)+15] = g ^= k[8*(i)+ 7]; \
305}
306#define kdl8(k,i) \
307{ ss[0] ^= ls_box(ss[7],3) ^ t_use(r,c)[i]; k[8*(i)+ 8] = ss[0]; ss[1] ^= ss[0]; k[8*(i)+ 9] = ss[1]; \
308 ss[2] ^= ss[1]; k[8*(i)+10] = ss[2]; ss[3] ^= ss[2]; k[8*(i)+11] = ss[3]; \
309}
310
311aes_rval aes_set_decrypt_key(const unsigned char in_key[], unsigned int klen, aes_ctx cx[1])
312{ aes_32t ss[8];
313 d_vars
314
315#if !defined(FIXED_TABLES)
316#ifdef GLOBALS
317 if(!t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs();
318#else
319 if(!cx->t_ptr || !t_use(in,it)) gen_tabs(cx);
320#endif
321#endif
322
323#if !defined(BLOCK_SIZE)
324 if(!cx->n_blk) cx->n_blk = 16;
325#else
326 cx->n_blk = BLOCK_SIZE;
327#endif
328
329 if(((klen & 7) || klen < 16 || klen > 32) && ((klen & 63) || klen < 128 || klen > 256))
330 {
331 cx->n_rnd = 0; return aes_bad;
332 }
333
334 klen >>= (klen < 128 ? 2 : 5);
335 cx->n_blk = (cx->n_blk & ~3) | 2;
336
337 cx->k_sch[0] = ss[0] = word_in(in_key );
338 cx->k_sch[1] = ss[1] = word_in(in_key + 4);
339 cx->k_sch[2] = ss[2] = word_in(in_key + 8);
340 cx->k_sch[3] = ss[3] = word_in(in_key + 12);
341
342#if (BLOCK_SIZE == 16) && (DEC_UNROLL != NONE)
343
344 switch(klen)
345 {
346 case 4:
347 kdf4(cx->k_sch, 0); kd4(cx->k_sch, 1);
348 kd4(cx->k_sch, 2); kd4(cx->k_sch, 3);
349 kd4(cx->k_sch, 4); kd4(cx->k_sch, 5);
350 kd4(cx->k_sch, 6); kd4(cx->k_sch, 7);
351 kd4(cx->k_sch, 8); kdl4(cx->k_sch, 9);
352 cx->n_rnd = 10; break;
353 case 6:
354 cx->k_sch[4] = ff(ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16));
355 cx->k_sch[5] = ff(ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20));
356 kdf6(cx->k_sch, 0); kd6(cx->k_sch, 1);
357 kd6(cx->k_sch, 2); kd6(cx->k_sch, 3);
358 kd6(cx->k_sch, 4); kd6(cx->k_sch, 5);
359 kd6(cx->k_sch, 6); kdl6(cx->k_sch, 7);
360 cx->n_rnd = 12; break;
361 case 8:
362 cx->k_sch[4] = ff(ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16));
363 cx->k_sch[5] = ff(ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20));
364 cx->k_sch[6] = ff(ss[6] = word_in(in_key + 24));
365 cx->k_sch[7] = ff(ss[7] = word_in(in_key + 28));
366 kdf8(cx->k_sch, 0); kd8(cx->k_sch, 1);
367 kd8(cx->k_sch, 2); kd8(cx->k_sch, 3);
368 kd8(cx->k_sch, 4); kd8(cx->k_sch, 5);
369 kdl8(cx->k_sch, 6);
370 cx->n_rnd = 14; break;
371 default:
372 ;
373 }
374#else
375 cx->n_rnd = (klen > nc ? klen : nc) + 6;
376 { aes_32t i, l;
377 l = (nc * cx->n_rnd + nc - 1) / klen;
378
379 switch(klen)
380 {
381 case 4:
382 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
383 ke4(cx->k_sch, i);
384 break;
385 case 6:
386 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
387 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
388 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
389 ke6(cx->k_sch, i);
390 break;
391 case 8:
392 cx->k_sch[4] = ss[4] = word_in(in_key + 16);
393 cx->k_sch[5] = ss[5] = word_in(in_key + 20);
394 cx->k_sch[6] = ss[6] = word_in(in_key + 24);
395 cx->k_sch[7] = ss[7] = word_in(in_key + 28);
396 for(i = 0; i < l; ++i)
397 ke8(cx->k_sch, i);
398 break;
399 default:
400 ;
401 }
402#if (DEC_ROUND != NO_TABLES)
403 for(i = nc; i < nc * cx->n_rnd; ++i)
404 cx->k_sch[i] = inv_mcol(cx->k_sch[i]);
405#endif
406 }
407#endif
408
409 return aes_good;
410}

412#endif
